claim.claim-text:
11. A semiconductor wafer comprising: 
a base wafer; 
an insulating layer arranged on said base wafer; 
a monocrystalline silicon layer arranged on said insulating layer; 
products formed on said monocrystalline silicon layer; and 
an ID mark formed on said base wafer and containing data including a properties, manufacturing conditions, and test results of said products.

19. A semiconductor wafer comprising: 
a circular first principal plane on which semiconductor device is formed; 
a reference ID mark formed on said wafer and indicating a crystal orientation of said wafer; 
a recess formed on the periphery of said wafer and having a bottom inclined with respect to said first principal plane; and 
an etch pit formed on said bottom and remaining after a polishing process carried out on said wafer, said etch pit being defined by second-orientation crystal faces that are different from first-orientation crystal faces exposed at said first principal plane.

20. A semiconductor wafer comprising: 
a circular base wafer; 
a bevel contour formed along the periphery of said base wafer; 
an insulating layer arranged on said base wafer; 
a monocrystalline silicon layer arranged on said insulating layer; and 
a reference position defined on the periphery of said monocrystalline silicon layer, to indicate a crystal orientation of said monocrystalline silicon layer.

26. An equipment for manufacturing semiconductor device, comprising: 
a wafer stage having a rotary mechanism; 
a light source to emit a light beam toward a rotation center of said wafer stage to irradiate a principal plane of a wafer set on said wafer stage; 
a detector to measure a intensity of scattered light from crystal defects on said wafer; 
a computer to analyze a rotation angle dependence of the measured intensity; 
a marking unit to form a reference ID mark on said wafer to indicate a crystal orientation of said wafer; and 
a chamber covering at least said wafer stage, wafer, light source, and detector, to block external light.

27. An equipment for manufacturing semiconductor device, comprising: 
a wafer stage; 
a light source to emit light onto a principal plane of a wafer set on said wafer stage; 
a photodetector having a photosensitive face surrounding an emission mouth of said light source and inclined with respect to an advancing direction of the emitted light, said photodetector measuring a intensity of scattered light from etch pits formed on said principal plane of said wafer; 
a computer to analyze a rotation angle dependence of the measured intensity; 
a marking unit to form a reference ID mark on said wafer, to indicate a crystal orientation of said wafer; and 
a chamber covering at least said wafer stage, wafer, light source, and photodetector, to block external light.

31. A method of manufacturing semiconductor device, comprising: 
forming a bevel contour along the periphery of a semiconductor wafer; 
forming products on said wafer; 
forming a first ID mark on said bevel contour, said first ID mark containing data including a properties, manufacturing conditions, and test results of said products; 
reading said first ID mark; and 
forming other products on said wafer according to a data read from said first ID mark.

36. A method of manufacturing semiconductor device, comprising: 
forming a recess on the periphery of a semiconductor wafer with a bottom of said recess being inclined with respect to a first principal plane of said wafer on which the semiconductor device is formed; 
forming an etch pit on said bottom by carrying out an etching process whose etching speed differs depending on crystal orientations of said wafer, said etch pit being defined with second-orientation crystal faces that are different from first-orientation crystal faces exposed at said first principal plane; 
determining a crystal orientation of said recess according to a shape of said etch pit; and 
forming a reference ID mark on said wafer, to indicate a crystal orientation of said wafer.

39. A method of manufacturing semiconductor device, comprising: 
emitting a light beam onto a principal plane of a wafer; 
measuring a intensity of scattered light from crystal defects in said wafer; 
analyzing a rotation angle dependence of the measured intensity; and 
determining a crystal orientation of said wafer according to the analyzed rotation angle dependence.

42. A method of manufacturing a semiconductor wafer, comprising: 
forming said wafer by slicing a monocrystalline ingot; 
removing undulation on a principal plane of said wafer by carrying out an etching process on said wafer, said etching process using an alkali solution and involving different etching speeds depending on crystal orientations; 
measuring a crystal orientation of said wafer according to etch pits formed on said principal plane by said etching process; 
forming a reference ID mark on said wafer, to indicate the measured crystal orientation of said wafer; and 
removing said etch pits.

43. A method of manufacturing a semiconductor wafer, comprising: 
forming a bevel contour along the periphery of a circular base wafer; 
forming a reference ID mark on said bevel contour, to indicate a crystal orientation of an SOI layer wafer; 
forming the SOI layer wafer having a reference position indicating the crystal orientation of said SOI layer wafer; 
forming an insulating layer on a first principal plane of said SOI layer wafer; and 
bonding said base wafer to a insulating layer side of said SOI layer wafer with said reference ID mark being aligned with said reference position.
